<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 10 at 6:08PM MDT until July 10 at 6:30PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 630 PM MDT
FOR EASTERN TETON...WESTERN CHOUTEAU AND NORTH CENTRAL CASCADE
COUNTIES...
At 607 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Great Falls,
moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Great Falls, Black Eagle, Malmstrom Afb, Vaughn, First Peoples
Buffalo Jump State Park and Ulm.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
